options(warn=-1)

Scatter plots

qplot(carat,price,data=diamonds)

qplot(log(carat),log(price),data=diamonds)

qplot(carat, x * y * z, data = diamonds)

Aesthetics : color,shape,size

set.seed(1)

k<-sample(c(1:nrow(diamonds)),0.1*nrow(diamonds),replace=FALSE)

qplot(carat, price, data = diamonds[k,], colour = color)

qplot(carat, price, data = diamonds[k,], shape = cut)

Transparency to observe the density

qplot(carat, price, data = diamonds, alpha = I(1/100))

Smoother plots

qplot(carat, price, data = diamonds[k,], geom = c("point", "smooth"))
## geom_smooth: method="auto" and size of largest group is >=1000, so using gam with formula: y ~ s(x, bs = "cs"). Use 'method = x' to change the smoothing method.

Method : loess

qplot(carat, price, data = diamonds[k,], geom = c("point", "smooth"),method='loess',
      span = 0.2)

Using Splines

library(splines)
qplot(carat, price, data = diamonds[k,], geom = c("point", "smooth"),
      method = "lm", formula = y ~ ns(x,5))

Jitter and Box plots

qplot(color, price / carat, data = diamonds, geom = "jitter",
      alpha = I(1 / 5))

qplot(color, price / carat, data = diamonds, geom = "boxplot")

# Histograms and Density plots

qplot(carat, data = diamonds, geom = "histogram",binwidth=0.1)

qplot(carat, data = diamonds, geom = "density")

qplot(carat, data = diamonds, geom = "histogram",binwidth=0.1,fill=color)

qplot(carat, data = diamonds, geom = "density",colour=color)

Bar graph

qplot(color, data = diamonds, geom = "bar",fill=color)

qplot(color, data = diamonds, geom = "bar",weight=carat)

Timeseries plotting

qplot(date, unemploy / pop, data = economics, geom = "line")

Faceting

qplot(carat, data = diamonds, facets = color ~ .,
      geom = "histogram", binwidth = 0.1, xlim = c(0, 3))

qplot(carat, data = diamonds, facets = color ~ .,
      geom = "density", binwidth = 0.1, xlim = c(0, 3))

qplot(carat,price, data = diamonds[k,], facets = color ~ .,
      geom = "point")
